---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Disclaimers | TikaTiles"
			description="Safety, prototype, and product disclaimers for TikaTiles."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="legal-page prose">
			<p class="legal-kicker">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>
			<h1>Disclaimers</h1>
			<p>
				TikaTiles is an early prototype project. The information on this website is provided
				to describe the concept, invite feedback, and show browser-based game ideas.
			</p>

			<h2>No Released Product Yet</h2>
			<p>
				Any physical tile product, mobile app, game library, developer API, battery system,
				wireless feature, spatial mapping behavior, LED display, audio feature, or haptic
				feature shown or described is subject to change.
			</p>

			<h2>Safety and Supervision</h2>
			<p>
				Future physical prototypes should be used only under appropriate adult supervision.
				Small parts, batteries, electronics, charging equipment, cords, bright lights, sound,
				and floor play can present risks if designed, used, stored, or supervised improperly.
			</p>

			<h2>Certifications</h2>
			<p>
				No statement on this website should be interpreted as a claim that any future product
				has completed toy safety, battery safety, radio, electrical, privacy, accessibility,
				or app store certification.
			</p>

			<h2>Educational Content</h2>
			<p>
				Game examples involving math, memory, puzzles, coding, or learning are illustrative.
				They are not a substitute for professional educational, medical, developmental, or
				therapeutic advice.
			</p>

			<h2>Third-Party Names</h2>
			<p>
				References to game styles, classic games, app stores, platforms, companies, or tools
				are for descriptive purposes only. TikaTiles is not affiliated with those third parties
				unless explicitly stated.
			</p>

			<h2>Legal Review</h2>
			<p>
				These website terms, privacy notes, and disclaimers are general starting points. They
				should be reviewed by qualified counsel before commercial launch, collection of child
				data, taking payments, shipping hardware, or publishing an app.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.legal-page {
		padding-top: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5rem);
	}

	.legal-kicker {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-indent: 0;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.legal-page h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 8vw, 5.5rem);
		line-height: 0.95;
	}

	.legal-page h2 {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 2rem);
	}

	.legal-page p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		text-indent: 0;
	}
</style>
